Sentencas: Information from ex situ characterization can fall short in describing complex materials systems simultaneously exposed to multiple external stimuli.
Titulo: Operando and In situ X-ray Spectroscopies of Degradation in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Thin Film Cathodes in Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Operando X-ray absorption spectroscopy (XAS) was used to probe the local atomistic and electronic structure of specific elements in a La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) thin film cathode exposed to air contaminated with H2O and CO2 under operating conditions.
Titulo: Operando and In situ X-ray Spectroscopies of Degradation in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Thin Film Cathodes in Fuel Cells

Sentencas: While impedance spectroscopy showed that the polarization resistance of the LSCF cathode increased upon exposure to both contaminants at 750 degrees C, XAS near-edge and extended fine structure showed that the degree of oxidation for Fe and Co decreases with increasing temperature.
Titulo: Operando and In situ X-ray Spectroscopies of Degradation in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Thin Film Cathodes in Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Synchrotron-based X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy tracked the formation and removal of a carbonate species, a Co phase, and different oxygen moieties as functions of temperature and gas.
Titulo: Operando and In situ X-ray Spectroscopies of Degradation in La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Thin Film Cathodes in Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The combined information provides insight into the fundamental mechanism by which H2O and CO2 cause degradation in the cathode of solid oxide fuel cells.
